  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Improving Shelter Standards for IDP Camps in Iraq</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project aims to cover critical gaps for Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) living in protracted displacement in two large and underserved camps in Iraq that are likely to remain open or serve as transition camps. IOM is supporting humanitarian partners and camp management agencies to maintain an adequate shelter standard in targeted camps by setting up a procurement of tents and tent replacement process over six months period. This aims to provide the camp population with an improved shelter standard and better living conditions that meet minimum protection and humanitarian standards.</narrative>
  </description>
